{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, as shown in some subplots in Figure S1, the number of training epochs could be less than the maximum number allowed (i.e., 100).",
    "This is because the nested validation performance was used to closely monitor the model training process, enabling early stopping when the model performance did not improve over time to avoid model overfitting.",
    "The final model testing performance was evaluated on the independent testing sets (not used during model training and nested validation) across ten folds.",
    "The mean AUC and AP scores and their standard deviations were calculated across all folds (see Fig. 9).",
    "Results have shown that the signed directed GNN model can achieve more than 97% classification accuracy on average (AUC = 0.977 and AP = 0.979)."
  ]
}